---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/docs-layout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/code-block.astro';
import ColorPicker from '../../components/color-picker.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Theming - DocyUI" description="Customize the look and feel of your DocyUI components">
  <div class="pb-12 pt-8">
    <div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-4 md:flex-row md:justify-between md:gap-8">
      <div class="flex-1 space-y-4">
        <h1 class="inline-block font-heading text-4xl tracking-tight lg:text-5xl">
          <span class="docyui-gradient-text">Theming</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Customize the look and feel of your DocyUI components with color palettes, design tokens, and themes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Interactive Color Picker -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading tracking-tight">Color Palettes</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        DocyUI comes with 11 carefully crafted color palettes. Click on any color to see a live preview and apply it to the documentation.
      </p>
      
      <ColorPicker selectedColor="slate" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Color Palette Information -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">Available Palettes</h3>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        Each palette includes carefully selected colors that work harmoniously together across light and dark themes.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Slate</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(215.4, 16.3%, 46.9%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(215.3, 19.3%, 34.5%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(215.4, 16.3%, 26.9%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Cool, professional gray-blue tones</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Gray</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(0, 0%, 45.1%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(0, 0%, 32.2%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(0, 0%, 14.9%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Pure neutral grays</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Zinc</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(240, 3.8%, 46.1%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(240, 5.9%, 33.9%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(240, 10%, 3.9%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Subtle blue-tinted grays</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Stone</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(25, 5.3%, 44.7%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(33.3, 5.5%, 32.4%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(20, 14.3%, 4.1%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Warm, earthy tones</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Red</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(0, 84.2%, 60.2%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(0, 93.5%, 50.4%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(0, 62.8%, 30.6%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Bold, energetic reds</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Orange</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(24.6, 95%, 53.1%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(20.5, 90.2%, 48.2%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(12, 76%, 61%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Vibrant, warm oranges</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Blue</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(221.2, 83.2%, 53.3%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(224, 76.3%, 48%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(224, 76.3%, 48%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Classic, trustworthy blues</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Green</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(142.1, 76.2%, 36.3%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(142.1, 70.6%, 45.3%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(142.4, 71.8%, 29.2%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Fresh, natural greens</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Yellow</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(47.9, 95.8%, 53.1%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(45.4, 93.4%, 47.5%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(35.5, 91.7%, 32.9%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Bright, cheerful yellows</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Violet</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(262.1, 83.3%, 57.8%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(263.4, 70%, 50.4%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(263.4, 70%, 50.4%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Royal, sophisticated purples</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-2">
          <div class="font-semibold">Rose</div>
          <div class="flex space-x-2">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(330, 81.2%, 60.4%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(336, 84.1%, 56.5%)"></div>
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded border" style="background-color: hsl(336, 84.1%, 56.5%)"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Elegant, romantic pinks</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Convention -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading tracking-tight">Convention</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        DocyUI uses a simple <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">background</code> and <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">foreground</code> convention for colors. The <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">background</code> variable is used for the background color of a component and the <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">foreground</code> variable is used for the text color.
      </p>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        The <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">background</code> suffix is omitted when the variable is used for the background color of the component.
      </p>
      
      <CodeBlock 
        react={`--primary: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
--primary-foreground: 210 40% 98%;`}
        vue={`--primary: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
--primary-foreground: 210 40% 98%;`}
        language="css"
        title="CSS Variables"
      />
      
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        The <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">primary</code> variable is used for the background color of the component and the <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">primary-foreground</code> variable is used for the text color.
      </p>
      
      <CodeBlock 
        react={`<div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
  Hello, world!
</div>`}
        vue={`<div class="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
  Hello, world!
</div>`}
        title="Usage Example"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- List of Variables -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading tracking-tight">List of Variables</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        Here's the list of variables available for customization:
      </p>
      
      <CodeBlock 
        react={`--background
--foreground
--card
--card-foreground
--popover
--popover-foreground
--primary
--primary-foreground
--secondary
--secondary-foreground
--muted
--muted-foreground
--accent
--accent-foreground
--destructive
--destructive-foreground
--border
--input
--ring
--radius
--chart-1
--chart-2
--chart-3
--chart-4
--chart-5`}
        vue={`--background
--foreground
--card
--card-foreground
--popover
--popover-foreground
--primary
--primary-foreground
--secondary
--secondary-foreground
--muted
--muted-foreground
--accent
--accent-foreground
--destructive
--destructive-foreground
--border
--input
--ring
--radius
--chart-1
--chart-2
--chart-3
--chart-4
--chart-5`}
        language="css"
        title="Available CSS Variables"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Adding New Colors -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading tracking-tight">Adding New Colors</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        To add new colors, you need to add them to your CSS file and your <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">tailwind.config.js</code> file.
      </p>
      
      <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">1. Add to CSS</h3>
      <CodeBlock 
        react={`:root {
  --warning: 38 92% 50%;
  --warning-foreground: 48 96% 89%;
}

.dark {
  --warning: 48 96% 89%;
  --warning-foreground: 38 92% 50%;
}`}
        vue={`:root {
  --warning: 38 92% 50%;
  --warning-foreground: 48 96% 89%;
}

.dark {
  --warning: 48 96% 89%;
  --warning-foreground: 38 92% 50%;
}`}
        language="css"
        title="global.css"
      />
      
      <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">2. Add to Tailwind Config</h3>
      <CodeBlock 
        react={`module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        warning: "hsl(var(--warning))",
        "warning-foreground": "hsl(var(--warning-foreground))",
      },
    },
  },
}`}
        vue={`module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        warning: "hsl(var(--warning))",
        "warning-foreground": "hsl(var(--warning-foreground))",
      },
    },
  },
}`}
        language="js"
        title="tailwind.config.js"
      />
      
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        You can now use the <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">warning</code> utility class in your components.
      </p>
      
      <CodeBlock 
        react={`<div className="bg-warning text-warning-foreground" />`}
        vue={`<div class="bg-warning text-warning-foreground" />`}
        title="Usage"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Other Color Formats -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading tracking-tight">Other Color Formats</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        DocyUI supports multiple color formats. While the default uses HSL values, you can use any format supported by CSS.
      </p>
      
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">Using RGB</h3>
        <CodeBlock 
          react={`:root {
  --primary: 255, 255, 255;
  --primary-foreground: 0, 0, 0;
}`}
          vue={`:root {
  --primary: 255, 255, 255;
  --primary-foreground: 0, 0, 0;
}`}
          language="css"
        />
        
        <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">Using OKLCH</h3>
        <CodeBlock 
          react={`:root {
  --primary: 0.65 0.23 34.6;
  --primary-foreground: 0.98 0.02 95.5;
}`}
          vue={`:root {
  --primary: 0.65 0.23 34.6;
  --primary-foreground: 0.98 0.02 95.5;
}`}
          language="css"
        />
        
        <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">Using HEX with Opacity</h3>
        <CodeBlock 
          react={`:root {
  --primary: #3b82f6;
}`}
          vue={`:root {
  --primary: #3b82f6;
}`}
          language="css"
        />
        
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Make sure to update your <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">tailwind.config.js</code> to use the correct CSS variable format.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CSS Variables -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading tracking-tight">CSS Variables</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        DocyUI components are styled using CSS variables, which makes it easy to customize the default colors and create custom themes.
      </p>
      
      <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">Enabling CSS Variables</h3>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        CSS variables are enabled by default when you initialize a new project. You can also enable them manually by setting <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">tailwind.cssVariables</code> to <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">true</code> in your <code class="text-sm bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">docyui.json</code> file.
      </p>
      
      <CodeBlock 
        react={`{
  "tailwind": {
    "cssVariables": true
  }
}`}
        vue={`{
  "tailwind": {
    "cssVariables": true
  }
}`}
        language="json"
        title="docyui.json"
      />
      
      <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">Using CSS Variables</h3>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        When CSS variables are enabled, components will use CSS variables instead of Tailwind CSS utility classes.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Without CSS Variables:</p>
          <CodeBlock 
            react={`<div className="bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-50" />`}
            vue={`<div class="bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-50" />`}
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">With CSS Variables:</p>
          <CodeBlock 
            react={`<div className="bg-background text-foreground" />`}
            vue={`<div class="bg-background text-foreground" />`}
          />
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-4">
        This approach gives you more flexibility to create custom themes without modifying component code.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  @reference "../../styles/global.css";
</style>